32void register_partition_types_bindings(pybind11::module &m) {
33 py::enum_<gridfire::partition::BasePartitionType>(m, "BasePartitionType")
34 .value("RauscherThielemann", gridfire::partition::BasePartitionType::RauscherThielemann)
35 .value("GroundState", gridfire::partition::BasePartitionType::GroundState)
36 .export_values();
37
38 m.def("basePartitionTypeToString", [](gridfire::partition::BasePartitionType type) {
39 return gridfire::partition::basePartitionTypeToString[type];
40 }, py::arg("type"), "Convert BasePartitionType to string.");
41
42 m.def("stringToBasePartitionType", [](const std::string &typeStr) {
43 return gridfire::partition::stringToBasePartitionType[typeStr];
44 }, py::arg("typeStr"), "Convert string to BasePartitionType.");
45}

47void register_ground_state_partition_bindings(pybind11::module &m) {
48 using GSPF = gridfire::partition::GroundStatePartitionFunction;
49 using PF = gridfire::partition::PartitionFunction;
50 py::class_<GSPF, PF>(m, "GroundStatePartitionFunction")
51 .def(py::init<>())
52 .def("evaluate", &gridfire::partition::GroundStatePartitionFunction::evaluate,
53 py::arg("z"), py::arg("a"), py::arg("T9"),
54 "Evaluate the ground state partition function for given Z, A, and T9.")
55 .def("evaluateDerivative", &gridfire::partition::GroundStatePartitionFunction::evaluateDerivative,
56 py::arg("z"), py::arg("a"), py::arg("T9"),
57 "Evaluate the derivative of the ground state partition function for given Z, A, and T9.")
58 .def("supports", &gridfire::partition::GroundStatePartitionFunction::supports,
59 py::arg("z"), py::arg("a"),
60 "Check if the ground state partition function supports given Z and A.")
61 .def("get_type", &gridfire::partition::GroundStatePartitionFunction::type,
62 "Get the type of the partition function (should return 'GroundState').");
63}
